column5: I think I will leave Stinky and Smelly at home tomorrow...  I had one good hit that peeled off about 4 feet of line then dropped the bait...the only other bumps were from the ducks and weeds catching the line in the current...
well at least ya got out, better luck tomorrow
Love your new mascots, Beans.  And it's great to hear that you're getting out.  I think that this is the first weekend that I've got out for some decent fishing this year myself.
They look like the little stinkers who altered the odor of my mutts on thursday.

I guess the odour from Stinky and Smelly lingered on from yesterday...one good hit but no runners today for me...  CPH landed one carp about fifteen pounds...looked good on him as he has been blanked three times this year already...
